  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Eastern Chad Recovery Program</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CRS and its partner S&#xE9;cours Catholique pour le D&#xE9;veloppement (SECADEV) propose five recovery activities: to provide cash vouchers-for-work (VFW) on community infrastructure projects, improve access to cowpea and reduce storage losses, facilitate access to horticulture seeds and off-season gardening, improve knowledge of agricultural and post-harvest techniques, and provide microfinance opportunities for income generating activities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the Eastern Chad Recovery Project, Catholic Relief Services (CRS) is helping 8,000 heads of household (46,400 people) build assets and diversify their livelihoods strategies so that they can recover from the 2012 food crisis, better adapt to changes, and mitigate future shocks. CRS will work with households who recently received Food for Peace-funded emergency food aid during the Sahel food crisis to ensure that they are viable and able to adapt to confront the next shock to their livelihoods.</narrative>
  </description>
